{# packs/events-management/templates/day-of-runbook.md.j2
   Jinja2 template for the day-of operations runbook.
   Generated by the registration-triage agent 24 hours before event start,
   or on demand via the admin UI.
   Delivered to event-team-slack output.

   Context variables:
     event.name               — event name
     event.starts_at          — event start datetime
     event.ends_at            — event end datetime
     event.venue              — venue name and address
     event.capacity           — declared capacity
     stats.confirmed_count    — confirmed registrants
     stats.waitlisted_count   — registrants on waitlist
     stats.vip_count          — VIP registrants
     stats.high_risk_count    — registrants flagged by no-show-predictor
     stats.fill_ratio         — confirmed / capacity (0.0–1.0)
     sessions                 — list of session objects (title, speaker, room, time, format)
     vip_registrants          — list of VIP registrant objects (name, email, dietary, access)
     flagged_registrants      — list of high-risk no-show registrants (name, email, prob)
     dietary_summary          — dict of dietary tag -> count
     accessibility_summary    — dict of accessibility tag -> count
     event_team               — list of team member objects (name, role, phone)
     venue_contacts           — list of venue contact objects (name, role, phone)
     emergency_contacts       — list of emergency contact objects (name, role, phone)
#}

# Day-of Runbook — {{ event.name }}

**Date:** {{ event.starts_at | date_format('%A, %B %-d, %Y') }}
**Time:** {{ event.starts_at | time_format('%H:%M') }} – {{ event.ends_at | time_format('%H:%M') }} (local venue time)
**Venue:** {{ event.venue | default('Virtual') }}
**Generated:** {{ now | datetime_format('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC') }}

